05071 #ifndef GLEXT_64_TYPES_DEFINED
05072 /* This code block is duplicated in glxext.h, so must be protected */
05073 #define GLEXT_64_TYPES_DEFINED
05074 /* Define int32_t, int64_t, and uint64_t types for UST/MSC */
05075 /* (as used in the GL_EXT_timer_query extension). */
05076 #if defined(__STDC_VERSION__) && __STDC_VERSION__ >= 199901L
05077 #include <inttypes.h>
05078 #elif defined(__sun__) || defined(__digital__)
05079 #include <inttypes.h>
05080 #if defined(__STDC__)
05081 #if defined(__arch64__) || defined(_LP64)
05082 typedef long int int64_t;
05083 typedef unsigned long int uint64_t;
05084 #else
05085 typedef long long int int64_t;
05086 typedef unsigned long long int uint64_t;
05087 #endif /* __arch64__ */
05088 #endif /* __STDC__ */
05089 #elif defined( __VMS ) || defined(__sgi)
05090 #include <inttypes.h>
05091 #elif defined(__SCO__) || defined(__USLC__)
05092 #include <stdint.h>
05093 #elif defined(__UNIXOS2__) || defined(__SOL64__)
05094 typedef long int int32_t;
05095 typedef long long int int64_t;
05096 typedef unsigned long long int uint64_t;
05097 #elif defined(_WIN32) && defined(__GNUC__)
05098 #include <stdint.h>
05099 #elif defined(_WIN32)
05100 typedef __int32 int32_t;
05101 typedef __int64 int64_t;
05102 typedef unsigned __int64 uint64_t;
05103 #else
05104 /* Fallback if nothing above works */
05105 #include <inttypes.h>
05106 #endif
05107 #endif

05111 typedef uint64_t GLuint64EXT;
